project.title: Aldecaldos + Badlands community
project.description:
One of the coolest tasks in an open-world game:  crowd designs. All gangs were split among different concept artists, together with Łukasz Poduch we were responsible for all nomads and badlands inhabitants, including the Aldecaldos and the Wraiths. Later we worked on the visual identity for them like logotypes, graffiti paintings and stickers. Also, we had to prepare detailed versions of new assets like clothes, gear, masks, etc. Here's a bunch of my concepts, hope you like them!

Art direction: Paweł Mielniczuk
Vehicles designs: Lukasz Poduch

project.title: Medieval Leaded Glass Window - Substance Source Signature Collection
project.description:
This is one of my personal favourites in the collection. I spent a lot of time working on the parameters in this substance, ensuring the various shape adjustments responded to each-other correctly. For example, when adjusting the frame thickness the scale of the internal frame updates to match, ensuring the window is always split into even sub-sections. This makes on-the-fly tweaking very pleasant. Want a thinner frame? No problem! The rest of the window will morph to accommodate. After the shape is set there are options for glass styles, and then a good variety of parameters to age or weather the window.

It is part of my Medieval themed Signature Collection for Substance Source which I had the pleasure of working on with the awesome people of the Substance Source team over at Adobe. I set myself a few goals for the set. The most important of which was thorough customisability of each material, I wanted each substance in the collection to have numerous parameters with variations of the main graph could easily be created to give the user a lot of flexibility to customise each material to the needs of their specific projects.
